SIMPLE: impervious
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Impervious
<hw>Im*per"vi*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>impervius</ets>; pref. <ets>im-</ets> not + <ets>per</ets> through
+ <ets>via</ets> way. See <er>Voyage</er>.]</ety> <def>Not pervious; not
admitting of entrance or passage through; <as>as, a substance
<ex>impervious</ex> to water or air</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This gulf impassable, <qex>impervious</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The minds of these zealots were absolutely
<qex>impervious</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Impassable; pathless; impenetrable; imperviable;
impermeable.</syn></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Im*per"vi*ous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Im*per"vi*ous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Impery</ent>⟦br⟧
